I";<h2 id="today-and-the-road-ahead">Today and the road ahead…</h2>

<p>As I came from civil/structural engineering, my scientific production and my background are cast by numerical analysis and applied math/physics. Nevertheless, today I’m moving towards <strong>Machine Learning (ML), Data-Driven Modelling (DDM), Data Science (DS) &amp; Dev</strong>. I realized that computer science (CS) and DS are much more innovative, inventive, fulfilling and challeging, a place where novelty lies and where I can aplly my ingenuity and analytical skills. So I’ve been not only studying CS and DS but also – regarding my formal education – researching ways to bring DS, DDM and ML into (civil) engineering, especially the to the research of complex structures and materials.</p>

<p>Hence my two main research subjects today are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Machine Learning and Data-Driven Modelling</li>
  <li>(Generalized/Extended) Finite Element Method</li>
</ul>

